{
  "stem": "1169.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we do everything that they-- when they graduate by us, they should be imbued with our heritage and that all of them should continue to yeshiva high school and to be proud members of our nation.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Our nation has a right to live, and to exist.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And every Jew should know who he is and-- and be very proud of it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went back [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for the very first time to Hungary this year.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A cousin of mine took me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] as I flew into Budapest, I saw the red, white, and green flag at the Budapest airport.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "All these dreadful feelings and events came back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I thought, I'm back in 1944.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And we were on a bus.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was together with much younger boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we went to visit the graves of the forefathers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And these boys put on cassettes, this happy music.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they clapped their hands.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And as we went by these cities, it came back to my mind, these were cities where there was vibrant Jewish life, rich Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Many of our cousins were rabbis there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I just couldn't take the music, and the happiness, and the joy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I told the girls, you know, girls, it's so kind of you to take me with you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But I cannot take the music.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I'm getting sick in my stomach.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
